\title{Backend design}
\date{2024-07-30}

\p{The flow of state through the backend is the most important thing to design first.}

\p{The database consists of}

\transclude{dev-000C}

\transclude{dev-000B}

\transclude{dev-000D}


\p{The frontend can search for refs via their metadata.}

\p{Given a ref, the frontend can can request the current automerge document for a ref. When this happens, the backend will either:}

\ol{
  \li{Produce the document from the in-memory map, if it exists in the in-memory map.}
  \li{Create a new document (with a new ID!) with state given by the head snapshot for the ref.}
}

\p{The frontend can also query all snapshots connected to a ref.}

\p{The frontend can push an arbitrary snapshot onto the head of an arbitrary ref. This can be used to "branch off" from a point in the history of any ref, by creating a new ref, and then setting its head to an earlier snapshot.}
